## Layout and tooling

| Item | Convention |
|------|------------|
| Root | **`frontend/e2e/`** (config: **`frontend/e2e/playwright.config.ts`**) |
| Spec files | **`feature-name.spec.ts`** — one file per feature or user flow (kebab-case stem) |
| Helpers | **`frontend/e2e/helpers/`** or **`frontend/e2e/fixtures/`** — shared navigation, auth stubs, test data |
| Package | **`@playwright/test`**, **`@playwright/mcp`** in **`frontend/e2e/package.json`** |
| Cursor MCP | **`.cursor/mcp.json`** → `playwright` server via `npx @playwright/mcp@latest` |
| Agent skills | **`.agents/skills/playwright-skill/`**, **`playwright-core/`**, **`playwright-ci/`**, **`playwright-cli/`** — install via step 5 |
| Reports | **`playwright-report/`**, **`test-results/`**, **`blob-report/`** are gitignored — do not commit |

**App targets (local):** default `baseURL` in **`frontend/e2e/playwright.config.ts`** is **`http://127.0.0.1:8802`** (**`frontend/`**). For **`aspire.svc/`** (8801), add a separate Playwright **project** or a future **`aspire.svc/e2e/`** workspace (see **`.cursor/rules/solution.mdc`**). Start the dev server in CI/global setup or document the prerequisite; do not hard-code stale ports (8081, 3000, etc.).

